Add a Zod-validated search schema to the dashboard index route in `apps/client/src/router.tsx` so that `/?detail=dead-letter&itemId=abc` URLs are parsed and validated.

## Implementation

Modify `apps/client/src/router.tsx`:

1. Add the dashboard search schema after the existing `sessionSearchSchema`:

```typescript
// ── Dashboard search param schema ──────────────────────────
const dashboardSearchSchema = z.object({
  detail: z.enum(['dead-letter', 'failed-run', 'offline-agent']).optional(),
  itemId: z.string().optional(),
});

/** Search params available on the `/` (dashboard) route. */
export type DashboardSearch = z.infer<typeof dashboardSearchSchema>;
```

2. Update the `indexRoute` definition to use `validateSearch`:

```typescript
const indexRoute = createRoute({
  getParentRoute: () => appShellRoute,
  path: '/',
  validateSearch: zodValidator(dashboardSearchSchema),
  component: DashboardPage,
  beforeLoad: ({ location }) => {
    const params = new URLSearchParams(location.searchStr);
    const session = params.get('session');
    if (session) {
      throw redirect({
        to: '/session',
        search: { session, dir: params.get('dir') ?? undefined },
      });
    }
  },
});
```

The only change to `indexRoute` is adding the `validateSearch: zodValidator(dashboardSearchSchema)` line. The existing `beforeLoad` with session redirect logic is preserved exactly as-is.

## Files Modified

- `apps/client/src/router.tsx` — add `dashboardSearchSchema`, export `DashboardSearch` type, add `validateSearch` to `indexRoute`

## Acceptance Criteria

- `DashboardSearch` type is exported from `router.tsx`
- Navigating to `/?detail=dead-letter&itemId=test` parses correctly (no validation errors)
- Navigating to `/?detail=invalid-value` strips the invalid value (Zod validation)
- Navigating to `/` with no search params works as before (both fields `undefined`)
- Existing `?session=` redirect still works (preserved in `beforeLoad`)
- `pnpm typecheck` passes
- The `zodValidator` import already exists in the file (used by `sessionRoute`), so no new import is needed

Extract the `formatRelativeTime` function from `AttentionItem.tsx` into a shared utility within the `dashboard-attention` feature module so that the new Sheet components can reuse it without importing from a UI file.

## Implementation

1. Create `apps/client/src/layers/features/dashboard-attention/lib/format-relative-time.ts`:

```typescript
/**
 * Format an ISO timestamp as a compact relative time string.
 *
 * @param iso - ISO 8601 timestamp string
 * @returns Relative time like "5m", "2h", or "3d"
 */
export function formatRelativeTime(iso: string): string {
  const diff = Date.now() - new Date(iso).getTime();
  const minutes = Math.floor(diff / 60000);
  if (minutes < 60) return `${minutes}m`;
  const hours = Math.floor(minutes / 60);
  if (hours < 24) return `${hours}h`;
  return `${Math.floor(hours / 24)}d`;
}
```

