Update `DashboardPage` to read `detail` and `itemId` search params from the URL and conditionally render the appropriate detail Sheet component.

## Implementation

Modify `apps/client/src/layers/widgets/dashboard/ui/DashboardPage.tsx`:

```typescript
import { ScrollArea } from '@/layers/shared/ui';
import { useSearch, useNavigate } from '@tanstack/react-router';
import {
  NeedsAttentionSection,
  DeadLetterDetailSheet,
  FailedRunDetailSheet,
  OfflineAgentDetailSheet,
} from '@/layers/features/dashboard-attention';
import { ActiveSessionsSection } from '@/layers/features/dashboard-sessions';
import { SystemStatusRow } from '@/layers/features/dashboard-status';
import { RecentActivityFeed } from '@/layers/features/dashboard-activity';

/**
 * Dashboard page — mission control overview composing feature sections.
 * Answers questions in priority order:
 * 1. Does anything need my attention?
 * 2. What is active right now?
 * 3. Is the system healthy?
 *
 * Orchestrator widget that composes feature-level sections in a scrollable container.
 * Reads `detail` and `itemId` search params to open attention item detail Sheets.
 */
export function DashboardPage() {
  const { detail, itemId } = useSearch({ strict: false });
  const navigate = useNavigate();

  const closeSheet = () =>
    navigate({
      to: '/',
      search: (prev) => ({ ...prev, detail: undefined, itemId: undefined }),
    });

  return (
    <ScrollArea className="h-full">
      <div className="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-8 px-6 py-8">
        <NeedsAttentionSection />
        <ActiveSessionsSection />
        <SystemStatusRow />
        <RecentActivityFeed />
      </div>

      <DeadLetterDetailSheet
        open={detail === 'dead-letter'}
        itemId={itemId}
        onClose={closeSheet}
      />
      <FailedRunDetailSheet
        open={detail === 'failed-run'}
        itemId={itemId}
        onClose={closeSheet}
      />
      <OfflineAgentDetailSheet
        open={detail === 'offline-agent'}
        onClose={closeSheet}
      />
    </ScrollArea>
  );
}
```

## Key Decisions

- `useSearch({ strict: false })` is used to access search params without strict route typing — this works because the route already validates via `zodValidator(dashboardSearchSchema)` from task 1.1
- `closeSheet` clears both `detail` and `itemId` from search params by setting them to `undefined`
- Using `search: (prev) => ({ ...prev, ... })` preserves any future search params that may be added
- The three Sheet components render as siblings after the main content — they are portaled via Sheet's built-in Portal so DOM position doesn't matter
- `OfflineAgentDetailSheet` does not receive `itemId` — it uses a sentinel value and shows all offline agents

## FSD Layer Compliance

- `widgets/dashboard` importing from `features/dashboard-attention` — allowed (widgets can import features)
- `widgets/dashboard` importing from `shared/ui` — allowed

## Files Modified

- `apps/client/src/layers/widgets/dashboard/ui/DashboardPage.tsx`

## Acceptance Criteria

- Navigating to `/?detail=dead-letter&itemId=slack::hop_limit` opens the DeadLetterDetailSheet
- Navigating to `/?detail=failed-run&itemId=run_abc123` opens the FailedRunDetailSheet
- Navigating to `/?detail=offline-agent&itemId=offline` opens the OfflineAgentDetailSheet
- Navigating to `/` with no search params shows no Sheets (all closed)
- Closing any Sheet clears `detail` and `itemId` from the URL
- Browser back button after opening a Sheet returns to `/` with no Sheet
- Existing dashboard sections (NeedsAttentionSection, ActiveSessionsSection, SystemStatusRow, RecentActivityFeed) render unchanged
- `pnpm typecheck` passes

